// Proving-gate fixture: MID-ITERATION DROP — the generator is dropped while
// suspended, holding owned heap values it never surfaced.
//
// The consumer breaks after the first value. The generator is suspended at the
// second yield holding "second-B" and never reaches "third-C". Dropping it must
// release exactly the live frame-owned values (no leak under LSan, no
// double-free under ASan) and must NOT print the unconsumed markers.
//
// Expected stdout: "first-A" then "after-break" — the unconsumed yields never
// print because their println side effects never fire (lazy). On the thread
// runtime the dropped generator's thread is cancelled + joined and its unsent
// mpsc values are drained; on the coro path the cleanup outline drops the
// frame-owned values. The observable behaviour is frozen across the migration.
fn main() {
    let g = gen {
        println("gen:first");
        yield "first" + "-A";
        println("gen:second");
        yield "second" + "-B";
        println("gen:third");
        yield "third" + "-C";
    };
    for s in g {
        println(s);
        break;
    }
    println("after-break");
}
